-%230094FF?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=maxAge&#x26;logo=youtube\" alt=\"duration\"> <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Duration:%20-61%20min-%230094FF?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=maxAge&#x26;logo=youtube\" alt=\"duration\"> February 14, 2022 - Blazor is a free and open-source web framework that enables developers to create web apps using C# and HTML. Being a .NET developer as well as a big fan of classic point-and-click adventure games, I’ve ported my Game-a-Tron 4000 adventure game engine to Blazor.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-05-12T11:56:06.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lGabdG5Ge8Y\">Blazor Basics with Identity</a> - <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Duration:%20-128%20min-%230094FF?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=maxAge&#x26;logo=youtube\" alt=\"duration\"> Mars 14, 2022 - Fritz shows you how to connect authentication and authorization to your Blazor app.  We'll focus on how to connect a properly configured Microsoft Identity application to your Blazor framework.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-05-12T11:41:44.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Rn8psTi8FBk\">Blazor, NET 6, and WebAssembly</a> - <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Duration:%20-60%20min-%230094FF?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=maxAge&#x26;logo=youtube\" alt=\"duration\"> February 21, 2022 - Talk by Steve Sanderson at the NDC Oslo 2021. .NET 6 is a huge release for Blazor, adding a ton of powerful new features for .NET web developers. This talk will be full of demos to get you up-to-speed on this hot framework.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-05-12T11:37:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://devblogs.microsoft.com/dotnet/asp-net-core-updates-in-dotnet-7-preview-4\">ASP.NET Core updates in .NET 7 Preview 4</a> - May 10, 2022 - .NET 7 Preview 4 is now available and includes many great new improvements to ASP.NET Core. Article by Dan Roth from Microsoft.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-05-12T11:34:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zS0y9krXO6E\">Building beautiful Blazor apps with Tailwind CSS</a> - <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Duration:%20-55%20min-%230094FF?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=maxAge&#x26;logo=youtube\" alt=\"duration\"> Mars 2, 2022 - Tailwind CSS has been growing in popularity for some time. It’s fast becoming one of the top frameworks to use when styling applications. It offers a different approach to the traditional frameworks like Bootstrap—utility based styling. Rather than using prebuilt components—which result in your application looking like a lot of others on the web—you can tailor your design by applying small focused CSS classes resulting in a unique style for your app. In this talk, you will learn how to bring the power of Tailwind CSS to your Blazor applications. We’ll start off with an introduction to Tailwind and how it differs from other CSS frameworks. Then we’ll get into some code and see how we can integrate Tailwind with Blazor. For the rest of the time, we’ll explore the various features of Tailwind and see how just how beautiful we can make our Blazor app. By Chris Sainty, at the NDC Oslo 2021.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-05-12T11:32:54.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Co7QetPYiO4\">Best practices unit testing Blazor components with bUnit</a> - <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Duration:%20-54%20min-%230094FF?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=maxAge&#x26;logo=youtube\" alt=\"duration\"> Mars 1, 2022 - Why create tests of UI components? Isn’t UI tests inherently brittle, run slowly, and hard to maintain? By Egil Hansen, at the NDC Oslo 2021.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-05-12T11:32:54.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mbiesiad/awesome-translations","categoryHTML":"<h2>Translations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20220511155347/https://github.com/JoseDeFreitas/awesome-translations/tree/es_ES\">Spanish</a></li>","updatedAt":"2022-05-12T11:20:04.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"academic/awesome-datascience","categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.manning.com/books/julia-for-data-analysis\">Julia for Data Analysis</a> - Early access</li>","updatedAt":"2022-05-12T08:15:33.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"rockerBOO/awesome-neovim","categoryHTML":"<h2>Plugin</h2><h4>Tree-sitter Supported Colorscheme</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/chrsm/paramount-ng.nvim\">chrsm/paramount-ng.nvim</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/chrsm/paramount-ng.nvim\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">5</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":5,\"repo\":\"chrsm/paramount-ng.nvim\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A dark color scheme written using Lush. Treesitter supported.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-05-12T07:23:36.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"HQarroum/awesome-iot","categoryHTML":"<h4>Miscellaneous</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/authbroker/authbroker\">authBroker</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/authbroker/authbroker\" style=\"text-decoration:none;t